{{Infobox football biography | playername = StÃ©phane Grichting | image = [[Image:StÃ©phane Grichting.jpg|150px]] | fullname = StÃ©phane Grichting | height = {{height|m=1.87}} | dateofbirth = {{Birth date and age|1979|03|30|df=y}} | cityofbirth = [[Sierre]] | countryofbirth = [[Switzerland]] | currentclub = [[AJ Auxerre|Auxerre]] | clubnumber = 4 | position = [[Defender (football)|Defender]] | youthyears1 = 1993â1996 |youthclubs1 = [[FC Sion|Sion]] | years1 = 1996â2002 |clubs1 = [[FC Sion|Sion]] |caps1 = 124 |goals1 = 5 | years2 = 2002â |clubs2 = [[AJ Auxerre|Auxerre]] |caps2 = 231 |goals2 = 1 | nationalyears1 = 2004â2011 | nationalteam1 = [[Switzerland national football team|Switzerland]] | nationalcaps1 = 45 | nationalgoals1 = 1 | pcupdate = 4 December 2011 | ntupdate = 06 June 2011 }} '''StÃ©phane Grichting''' (born 30 March 1979 in [[Sierre]]) is a [[Switzerland|Swiss]] [[Association football|football]] [[Defender (football)|defender]] who plays for [[AJ Auxerre|Auxerre]].
He currently has 36 [[cap (football)|cap]]s for the [[Switzerland national football team|Swiss national team]],<ref>http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/world_cup_2010/groups_and_teams/team/switzerland</ref> and was called up to the [[2006 FIFA World Cup]] and [[2010 FIFA World Cup]] squads. He was in the squad for the [[2004 European Football Championship]], but pulled out due to injury.
After Switzerland beat Turkey in the deciding qualifier to [[2006 FIFA World Cup]], he was injured in the riots that occurred after the match.
